{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:50+0000", "md5": "56ADBAFFE82FF985A1B9D0CF1B21D5E8", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 9}, "context": "STATCHECK builds upon the open-source code base of (Cao et al., 2018;Duc Cao et al., 2019). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.002898991107940674}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.220008850097656e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "StatClaim", "normalizedForm": "StatClaim", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 9}, "context": "StatClaim performs better than the original at detecting INSEE verifiable claims, and CheckWorthyClaim vastly outperforms both models on the detection of numerical claims, as they are a subset of check-worthy sentences that the model was trained to detect. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00041669607162475586}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.728534698486328e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05820709466934204}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 9}, "context": "STATCHECK is in daily use in the factchecking team; Figure 3 illustrates its GUI.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0874670147895813}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.940696716308594e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "StatClaim", "normalizedForm": "StatClaim", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 13}, "context": "Our StatClaim was used in its default configuration: extractions with numerical values and without verbs conjugated in the future or in the first person. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9667509198188782}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005181431770324707}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05820709466934204}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "normalizedForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 20}, "context": "For CheckWorthyClaim, a tweet is considered positive if the model returns a checkworthy score > 0.9.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0014851689338684082}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.510185241699219e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.53131103515625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 6, "offsetEnd": 15}, "context": "Thus, STATCHECK allows them to turn the future and first-person filters on and off.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.605552673339844e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0018338561058044434}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 12, "offsetEnd": 21}, "context": "By default, STATCHECK uses StatClaim for statistical claim detection. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 17, "offsetEnd": 26}, "context": "We developed the STATCHECK tool, which allows the journalist authors to focus their attention directly on check-worthy statements falling into one of two overlapping classes: those that can be checked based on statistics from two major institutions; and those that human users find interesting, even if the data to back up the checks is not present in the database. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.042552947998047e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996520280838013}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FlashText", "normalizedForm": "FlashText", "offsetStart": 20, "offsetEnd": 29}, "context": "We have adopted the FlashText algorithm (Singh, 2017), capable of finding, in a dataset metadata of size N , one of M fixed keywords in O(N ) time complexity. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.608268737792969e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9993122816085815}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.608268737792969e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9993122816085815}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 21, "offsetEnd": 30}, "context": "This paper describes STATCHECK, a statistic fact-checking system jointly developed by the authors, which are either computer science researchers or fact-checking journalists working for a French-language media with a daily audience of more than 15 millions (aud,  2022). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001430511474609375}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9990763664245605}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 25, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "The technical novelty of STATCHECK is twofold: (i) we focus on multidimensional, complex-structure statistics, which have received little attention so far, despite their practical importance; and (ii) novel statistical claim extraction modules for French, an area where few resources exist. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.424022674560547e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.759149968624115}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "StatClaim", "normalizedForm": "StatClaim", "offsetStart": 25, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "Evaluation procedure For StatClaim and Orig-inalStatClaim, a tweet is considered positive if models return at least one extracted statistical statement. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.26938867568969727}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05820709466934204}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "StatClaim", "normalizedForm": "StatClaim", "offsetStart": 27, "offsetEnd": 36}, "context": "By default, STATCHECK uses StatClaim for statistical claim detection. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05820709466934204}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "normalizedForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "offsetStart": 39, "offsetEnd": 55}, "context": "However, given the good performance of CheckWorthyClaim on numerical claims, we allow users to switch to it, even if we might not be able to verify them against the reference datasets.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006598830223083496}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.53131103515625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.53131103515625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 56, "offsetEnd": 65}, "context": "In our continuing collaboration, we will work to extend STATCHECK with more multidimensional statistic datasets from national governments and international organizations. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.000283658504486084}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996504783630371}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "StatClaim", "normalizedForm": "StatClaim", "offsetStart": 76, "offsetEnd": 85}, "context": "We refer to the two methods as OriginalStatClaim (Duc Cao et al., 2019) and StatClaim. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.011315882205963135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05820709466934204}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05820709466934204}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "StatClaim", "normalizedForm": "StatClaim", "offsetStart": 84, "offsetEnd": 93}, "context": "We evaluate the claim detection models, (Origi-nalStatClaim (Duc Cao et al., 2019), StatClaim and CheckWorthyClaim), on a set of 1595 tweets.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05820709466934204}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "normalizedForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "offsetStart": 98, "offsetEnd": 114}, "context": "We evaluate the claim detection models, (Origi-nalStatClaim (Duc Cao et al., 2019), StatClaim and CheckWorthyClaim), on a set of 1595 tweets.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.53131103515625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 109, "offsetEnd": 118}, "context": "Thus, unlike prior systems (Chen et al., 2020;Herzig et al., 2020;Jo et al., 2019;Karagiannis et al., 2020), STATCHECK does not compute a \"true/false\" verdict, leaving this tasks to journalists. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.001061856746673584}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.6702880859375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HeidelTime", "normalizedForm": "HeidelTime", "offsetStart": 112, "offsetEnd": 148}, "context": "The statistical entities and units are retrieved using exact string matching, while the date is extracted using HeidelTime (Str\u00f6tgen and Gertz, 2010), a time expression parser. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999673366546631}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.245208740234375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999673366546631}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.245208740234375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "normalizedForm": "CheckWorthyClaim", "offsetStart": 132, "offsetEnd": 148}, "context": "We report the results in Table 2 and Table 3. StatClaim performs better than the original at detecting INSEE verifiable claims, and CheckWorthyClaim vastly outperforms both models on the detection of numerical claims, as they are a subset of check-worthy sentences that the model was trained to detect.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.18878114223480225}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.6106834411621094e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978545308113098}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.53131103515625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Excel", "normalizedForm": "Excel", "offsetStart": 137, "offsetEnd": 142}, "context": "INSEE publishes each statistic report as an HTML page containing a description (title and comments on the data), and statistic tables in Excel or in HTML. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.002674698829650879}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.867813110351562e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.002674698829650879}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.867813110351562e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 138, "offsetEnd": 147}, "context": "In our collaboration between computer scientists and fact-checking journalists, we have developed, deployed, and continue to be extending STATCHECK, a fact-checking system specialized in the French media arena. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00014829635620117188}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 175, "offsetEnd": 184}, "context": "Different from (Chen et al., 2020;Herzig et al., 2020;Jo et al., 2019;Karagiannis et al., 2020;Ciampaglia et al., 2015;Nie et al., 2019;Yoneda et al., 2018;Aly et al., 2021), STATCHECK also includes a claim detection step, which saves journalists' time by focusing their attention on the claims worth checking; our claim detection module significantly outperforms the only one we know of for French (Duc Cao et al., 2019).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.10046839714050293}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.4781951904296875e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.5497207641601562e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 199, "offsetEnd": 208}, "context": "Below, we start by presenting a set of functional requirements derived from the journalist authors' experience in Section 2. Next, we describe the actual organization of statistic databases, and the STATCHECK architecture, in Section 3. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.1952797770500183}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06698369979858398}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "STATCHECK", "normalizedForm": "STATCHECK", "offsetStart": 228, "offsetEnd": 237}, "context": "Eurostat publishes 6,803 statistic tables, ranging from 2 lines to 37 million lines, and 580 dictionaries that, together, decode 243,083 statistical concepts codes into natural-language descriptions, all of which we acquired in STATCHECK' database. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006527304649353027}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00027555227279663086}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.41672515869140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997969269752502}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.008793532848358154}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 13866, "id": "14e32c980578e44169bec3ee7edd38f2b98e6e5c", "metadata": {"id": "14e32c980578e44169bec3ee7edd38f2b98e6e5c"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-03791175.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-03791175.grobid.tei.xml"}